<refentry>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>sum</refname>
    <refpurpose>Sum attribute values</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis><command>SELECT</command> * <command>FROM</command> sum(<replaceable>array</replaceable>,<replaceable>attribute</replaceable><optional>,<replaceable>dimension1</replaceable>,<replaceable>dimension2</replaceable>,...</optional>)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>Summary</title>
    <note>
      <para>The sum operator offers the same functionality as the sum aggregate.
See sum aggregate reference page for more information.</para>
    </note>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>Example</title>
    <informalexample>
      <para>This example sums the columns and rows of a 3<symbol role="symbolfont">&times;</symbol>3 array.</para>
      <procedure>
        <step>
          <para>Create a 1-attribute, 2-dimensional array called m3x3:<programlisting>CREATE ARRAY m3x3 &lt;val:double&gt;[i=0:2,3,0,j=0:2,3,0];</programlisting></para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Store values of 0&ndash;8 in m3x3:<programlisting>store(build(m3x3,i*3+j),m3x3);</programlisting><screen>[
[(0),(1),(2)],
[(3),(4),(5)],
[(6),(7),(8)]
]</screen></para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Sum the values of m3x3 along dimension j. This sums the columns of m3x3:<programlisting>sum(m3x3,val,j);</programlisting>This query outputs:<screen>[(9),(12),(15)]</screen></para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Sum the values of m3x3 along dimension i. This sums the rows of m3x3:<programlisting>sum(m3x3,val,i);</programlisting>This query outputs:<screen>[(3),(12),(21)]</screen></para>
        </step>
      </procedure>
    </informalexample>
  </refsect1>
</refentry>
